result.execSummary:
The defendant SEAN MICHAEL KRONBERG was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Interfere w/ Child Custody, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.31(2).
  • 2nd Degree Sexual Assault of Child, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.02(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: The Court ordered that all court costs, fines, and surcharges be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.   Penalty for non-payment shall be entry of civil judgment.   Clerk of Courts shall docket without fees.  Send payments to:  Clerk of Courts, Room 110, 415 Jackson Street, P O Box 2808, Oshkosh WI  54903-2808.

Pay all fees and costs.
Follow all rules of supervision.
Counseling as deemed appropriate including COMPAS assessment, AODA assessment, psychological treatment, sex offender treatment.
Maintain absolute sobriety.  No possession or consumption of alcohol or drugs/drug paraphernalia without a valid prescription.
No entering any taverns or bars.
No contact with V-1 or V-1's family.
No contact with any minors under the age of 18 years old other than Defendant's own family members.  
Provide DNA sample, if not previously submitted.
Comply with sex offender registry law.
